<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10618&amp;p=119939#p119939"><![CDATA[
GIFs are quantized to multiples of 10ms between frames. So you can accurately simulate what it would look like on a PAL TV on a monitor that ran at 50Hz (or a multiple), but nothing else quantizes nicely.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Sun Oct 27, 2013 12:06 pm</p><hr />
