<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Would it work? (palette trick)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10618&amp;p=119898#p119898"><![CDATA[
Those threads deals with multicolored, layered sprites. My idea is for 3 color (except transparency) sprites that have colors outside of standard NES palette:<br /><br /><img src="http://i.imgur.com/kXc7mu5.gif" alt="Image" /><br /><br />As you can see, result sprite (bottom) changes palette between first and second one which in return gives out color in between those used in both palettes. In theory, you could use this method to get more colors as long as two NES colors can be mixed together, 1:1 to get it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4924">darkhog</a> — Sat Oct 26, 2013 6:59 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
