<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10618&amp;p=119893#p119893</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10618&amp;p=119893#p119893"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Would it work? (palette trick)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10618&amp;p=119893#p119893"><![CDATA[
I was thinking about it for some time. Basically trick is based on &quot;half-transparency&quot; one, where sprite is being drawn every second frame (either odd or even ones). If we'd change palette of sprite every second frame, altering it so fast that human eye can't notice it, we could in theory &quot;mix&quot; NES palette's colors to achieve shades that are normally outside NES range. What do you think?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4924">darkhog</a> — Sat Oct 26, 2013 6:18 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
